Description: Floor sherd (with top of thin-walled pedestal foot) of Attic black-glazed pottery open vessel (cup-skyphos?); wholly glazed save for thin band at top of inside of foot; added red at top of stem outside. Possibly cut down to form a disc. Inscription incised on underside.
Curator's comments: British Museum 1910,0222.125 is from a similar, slightly smaller, cup, though the wall of the collar is a little thicker.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 526)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1586)
